# Micro-Lab: Multi-VLAN Inter-VLAN Routing & Dynamic DHCP Deployment

## 📌 Project Overview
This micro-lab demonstrates the implementation of a segmented local area network (LAN) using Layer 2 VLAN partitioning, Variable Length Subnet Masking (VLSM) using a `/26` boundary, and automated IP addressing via a Cisco IOS Router configured as a centralized DHCP server. Inter-VLAN traffic routing is achieved using a Router-on-a-Stick (RoaS) topology.

